Dataset Access
The project uses the BBC News Dataset.

Option 1: Download from Kaggle
You can download the dataset from Kaggle:

URL: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/crowdflower/bbc-news-data

Place the CSV file (bbc-text.csv) in the following path:

data/bbc-text.csv
Option 2: Use Sample Data Provided
If you are using the included sample or preprocessed dataset:

Ensure that the data/ folder exists and contains the CSV.

File structure:


project_root/
│
├── data/
│   └── bbc-text.csv
│
├── notebooks/
│   └── newsbot_midterm.ipynb

Running the Code
Clone the repository or download the project folder.

Place the dataset in the /data directory.

Open the Jupyter notebook under /notebooks and run each cell in sequence.
